dfischer.utils

Interface ThreadStepInterface


  • public interface ThreadStepInterface
    Asks a thread (concurrent user) about its current execution step (thread step). Used to make snapshots over the activity of all concurrent users during the load test.
    See Also:
    PerformanceData.dump(boolean), PerformanceData.dumpTo(java.io.PrintStream, boolean)

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int THREAD_NO_STEP
      The thread executes currently no step (not started, temporarily inactive or already completed).

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getExecutionStep()
      Returns the actual execution step of the thread (index of URL call or page break).

    • Field Detail
